Maintainer: C. William Yao <chun.william.yao.cnmtl@ssss.gouv.qc.ca>
Description: Cross-Continental travel and local daylight saving practice can introduce time shift, leading to biases in interpretation of the wearable measures when left without proper adjustment. This package streamlines data processing and analyses for longitudinal recordings. Together with additional features such as exporting daily wearable measures and visual reports, it aims to facilitate research on longitudinal wearable measures. To learn how to use it, check the vignettes for a quick tutorial. This tool is developed based on the methodology described in: Varesco, G. Yao, C. W., Dubé, E., Simonelli, G., Bieuzen, F. (2024) <doi:10.1113/ep092195>.
